content:
A toggle widget allows dashboard viewers to filter results based on a dimension. It requires a query with a single grouping and shows values as toggle options.

Drag the toggle widget to the canvas, select a field for the dimensions, and click Create. Behind the scenes, CRM Analytics creates a query grouped by the selected field. The query is added to the panel, making it available for other widgets.

To customize the widget, expand sections in the Widget panel and set styling properties for all or selected toggle options. To show query properties, click Query in the right panel and configure selection settings as needed. Viewers can select a toggle option to filter results and undo or change selections while viewing the dashboard.

Keyboard shortcuts for building CRM Analytics dashboards and lenses are available.
title: Add a Toggle Widget to Filter CRM Analytics Results
